The paper discusses a new metric for quantifying publication output of research groups, which can be used in support of ranking research groups or programs. The focus is on computer science research, specifically on CS graduate programs in Brazil. The paper mentions variables such as research results and impact, which are commonly associated with sub-categories such as cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.DB (Databases). The paper also discusses the comparison of publication output of research groups, which is relevant to sub-categories such as cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.CR, and cs.AI.
